The practical exercise includes reading and analysing scholarly reviews on the field of humanities. It results in learning how a review is to be written.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Students will train the writing of academic reviews on scholarly publications (books and articles) on the academic field of humanities, especially historical sciences. The topic includes reviews for publication in academic journal and also internal peer reviews. The practical exercises support achieving elementary skills for critical reading and evaluating of scholarly literature and proper presentation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student gains and improves his/her skills of independent critical evaluation of scholarly publications. As a result a original, potentially professionally publishable review of a relevant book will be written.
